  <section>
    <h2>Structure and styling</h2>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <p>The class names of the structure of a panel are shown to the right.</p>
        <p>Panel body content is only rendered if the panel is open.</p>
        <p>
          The panel, toggle and body all get the <code>fcp-is-open</code> class when the panel is open.
          This is so you can style each piece based on the state of the panel - descendent selectors can get tricky since you can nest panels.
        </p>
        <p>
          Finally, if you want to add padding to the body, target <code>.fcp-panel-body-inner</code>.
          Changing the height of the <code>.fcp-panel-body</code> itself will interfere with the animation.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Sample styling</strong></p>
        <p>Here's the default markup and styling used for the panels in this site:</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">

<pre>&lt;!-- closed panel --&gt;
&lt;div class='fcp-panel'&gt;
  &lt;a href='#' class='fcp-panel-toggle'&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;div class='fcp-panel-body'&gt;
    &lt;!-- content is not rendered --&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- open panel --&gt;
&lt;div class='fcp-panel <span class='code-highlight'>fcp-is-open</span>'&gt;
  &lt;a href='#' class='fcp-panel-toggle <span class='code-highlight'>fcp-is-open</span>'&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;div class='fcp-panel-body <span class='code-highlight'>fcp-is-open</span>'&gt;
    &lt;div class='fcp-panel-body-inner'&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

      </div>
